This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommender systems that rely on user-item interactions and unstructured text data. It also involves natural language processing techniques to learn word embeddings. Additionally, it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves text processing and semantic analysis. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with user preferences and interactions.
